Subject: [PATCH] PageTreeRepository: skip missing mount point records

When the page tree filter (AJAX `/typo3/ajax/page/tree/filterData`) runs in
a workspace whose `db_mountpoints` reference a deleted/non-existent page
record, `BackendUtility::getRecordWSOL('pages', $mountPoint)` returns NULL.
The subsequent `$pages[$mountPoint]['uid']` access then triggers a
PHP 8 "Trying to access array offset on value of type null" warning, which
the TYPO3 error handler promotes to an uncaught exception (#1476107295).

This patch hardens the loop so that mount points pointing at records that
cannot be resolved are skipped silently instead of producing a fatal.

Affected file:
  Classes/Tree/Repository/PageTreeRepository.php

--- a/Classes/Tree/Repository/PageTreeRepository.php
+++ b/Classes/Tree/Repository/PageTreeRepository.php
@@ -754,11 +754,17 @@ protected function filterPagesOnMountPoints(array $pages, array $mountPoints): a
         }
         // Make sure the mountpoints show up in page tree even when parent pages are not accessible pages
         foreach ($mountPoints as $mountPoint) {
-            if ($mountPoint !== 0) {
-                if (!array_key_exists($mountPoint, $pages)) {
-                    $pages[$mountPoint] = BackendUtility::getRecordWSOL('pages', $mountPoint);
-                    $pages[$mountPoint]['uid'] = (int)$pages[$mountPoint]['uid'];
+            if ($mountPoint === 0) {
+                continue;
+            }
+            if (!array_key_exists($mountPoint, $pages)) {
+                $record = BackendUtility::getRecordWSOL('pages', $mountPoint);
+                if (!is_array($record)) {
+                    // Mount point references a deleted or otherwise unresolvable page – skip it.
+                    continue;
                 }
-                $pages[$mountPoint]['pid'] = 0;
+                $pages[$mountPoint] = $record;
+                $pages[$mountPoint]['uid'] = (int)$pages[$mountPoint]['uid'];
             }
+            $pages[$mountPoint]['pid'] = 0;
         }
 
         return $pages;
